article.headline: Stony Brook 70, Maine 59
article.story: ORONO, Maine (AP)) -- Muhammad El-Amin scored 22 points and Demetrius Young added 17 as Stony Brook pulled away from Maine at the end of the first half en route to a 70-59 victory Tuesday night in America East. After Maine scored seven straight points to take a 24-23 lead, Stony Brook (13-10, 5-5) went on a 14-5 run to close the half, and Maine (8-15, 3-7) never got closer than six again. El-Amin, who had 16 points in the first half, hit one of his four 3-pointers in the half to put the Seawolves ahead 28-24, and Young scored the last nine points of the spurt for a 37-29 lead. The margin reached 55-41 before Maine pulled within six with 4:26 left, but the Black Bears could get no closer. Sean McNally led Maine with 15 points and Gerald McLemore added 14.
